title: Launch Roundup: NASA Crew-9 to fly half-empty, Starlink and Chinese launches continue
summary: NASA and SpaceX’s launch of the Crew-9 mission will be center stage this week. The launch of two new International Space Station crew members is currently scheduled for Thursday from the recently crew-certified Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station (CCSFS).
